    "summary": "On March 31, 2019 at approximately 1745 hours, an employee was injured while attempting to step down from a firewater pump skid. The employee entered the skid to address a coolant release, climbed down a fixed ladder, and mistakenly stepped onto the skid edge (17 inches high) instead of the grating, falling forward and sustaining a fractured left wrist.",
